373
00:25:02,229 --> 00:25:05,437
Fedot Ivanovich, I'll take this and then we'll leave at once?

374
00:25:08,104 --> 00:25:08,979
Kha, take it.

375
00:25:08,979 --> 00:25:11,354
I don't need him.

376
00:25:11,354 --> 00:25:12,854
(Rudnikov) Maykov!

377
00:25:12,854 --> 00:25:17,313
All right, I want this place searched,
and then lock it down and don't let anyone in.

378
00:25:17,646 --> 00:25:20,646
Take the bird, or it will die. Do it!

379
00:25:20,855 --> 00:25:23,521
(Stanislavsky) Wait,

380
00:25:23,521 --> 00:25:25,146
Check it out,

381
00:25:25,146 --> 00:25:26,938
Who's that?

382
00:25:26,938 --> 00:25:29,938
Like who. It's the Rajah himself.

383
00:25:30,438 --> 00:25:33,438
Yes.... It's been over 10 years,

384
00:25:34,063 --> 00:25:37,064
and he hasn't changed at all.

385
00:25:37,230 --> 00:25:40,105
And he sailed on the steamship Petersburg?

386
00:25:40,105 --> 00:25:40,814
Who knows.

387
00:25:41,855 --> 00:25:43,855
Maybe I did.

388
00:25:43,855 --> 00:25:46,314
His life is a mystery.

389
00:25:46,314 --> 00:25:49,147
And now, it's going to go away altogether.

390
00:25:49,147 --> 00:25:52,148
Let's go.

391
00:26:02,187 --> 00:26:02,356
So what, they're gonna find the killer now?

392
00:26:02,356 --> 00:26:03,690
I don't think so.

393
00:26:03,690 --> 00:26:05,356
I don't think Raja has any relatives.

394
00:26:05,356 --> 00:26:08,773
Soon, his assets will be dispersed into offices,
and he'll be safely forgotten.

395
00:26:09,398 --> 00:26:11,607
But it's a fascinating case.

396
00:26:11,607 --> 00:26:14,357
First of all, you have to figure it out,

397
00:26:14,357 --> 00:26:16,899
what this mysterious toothpick is.

398
00:26:16,899 --> 00:26:19,815
And can you die from such a small wound?

399
00:26:19,815 --> 00:26:21,607
Uh, hold on.

400
00:26:21,607 --> 00:26:23,815
Take a closer look.

401
00:26:23,815 --> 00:26:26,399
The sharp end is a different color.

402
00:26:26,399 --> 00:26:29,399
Maybe it's lubricated with something?

403
00:26:30,357 --> 00:26:32,066
It's possible.

404
00:26:32,066 --> 00:26:35,066
I know someone who can help us figure it out.

405
00:27:01,817 --> 00:27:04,817
(Gilyarovsky) Professor! He's always being carried around somewhere.

406
00:27:05,234 --> 00:27:06,026
Professor!

407
00:27:06,026 --> 00:27:07,776
Where'd he go?

408
00:27:07,776 --> 00:27:09,567
Professor!
